Mevociclib (SY-1365) is a selective CDK7 inhibitor. Mevociclib exhibits anti-proliferative and apoptotic effects in solid tumor cell lines. Mevociclib possesses anti-tumor activity in hematological and multiple aggressive solid tumors.
NVP-2 is a potent and selective ATP-competitive cyclin dependent kinase 9 (CDK9) probe. NVP-2 induces cell apoptosis.
AGI-5198 (IDH-C35) is a potent and selective mutant IDH1 R132H inhibitor
BMS641 (BMS-209641) is a selective RARbeta agonist.
BMS 753 is an isotype-selective retinoic acid receptor alpha (RARalpha) agonist
BMS961 is a selective retinoic acid receptor gamma (RARgamma) agonist

CMS-121 is a quinolone derivative and an orally active acetyl-CoA carboxylase 1 (ACC1) inhibitor. CMS-121 protects HT22 cells against ischemia and oxidative damage. CMS-121 has strong neuroprotective, anti-inflammatory, antioxidative and renoprotective activities.
Pinometostat (EPZ-5676) is a potent DOT1L histone methyltransferase inhibitor.

GSK547 (GSK'547) is a highly selective and potent inhibitor of receptor-interacting serine/threonine protein kinase 1 (RIPK1), inhibits macrophage-mediated adaptive immune tolerance in pancreatic cancer.
GSK591 (EPZ015866) is a potent and selective inhibitor of protein methyltransferase 5 (PRMT5).

GSK805 is an orally active and CNS penetrant RORgammat inhibitor. GSK805 inhibits RORgamma and Th17 cells differentiation. GSK805 inhibits the function of Th17 cells. GSK805 can be used for the research of immunity.

PLX5622 is a highly selective brain penetrant and orally active CSF1R inhibitor. PLX5622 allows for extended and specific microglial cells elimination, preceding and during pathology development. PLX5622 demonstrates desirable PK properties in varies animals. PLX5622 is mostly used in the way of feed free diet.

PNU-282987 is a potent alpha7 nicotinic acetylcholine receptor (nAChR) agonist. PNU-282987 is also a functional antagonist of the 5-HT3 receptor. PNU-282987 can be used for the research of central and peripheral nervous systems.
TAK-418 is a selective, orally active LSD1 (KDM1A) enzyme inhibitor. TAK-418 unlocks aberrant epigenetic machinery and improves autism symptoms in neurodevelopmental disorder models.
A dihydroxyflavone that is chrysin substituted by a prenyl group at position 8.

A member of the class of indoles that is 1H-indole substituted by a 5-chloro-2-[3-(4-{[(2E)-4-(dimethylamino)but-2-enoyl]amino}benzamido)anilino]pyrimidin-4-yl group at position 3. It is a selective and potent covalent inhibitor of CDK7 that exhibits anti-proliferative effects in cancer cell lines.
TMP269 is a novel and selective class IIa histone deacetylase (HDAC) inhibitor.
TMP778 is a potent and selective RORgt inverse agonist.
TMP920 is a highly potent and selective RORgt antagonist. TMP920 inhibits RORgt binding to the SRC1 peptide.
UNC1999 is a SAM-competitive, potent and selective inhibitor of EZH2/1.
X5050 is a REST inhibitor.

Apilimod (STA 5326) is a potent IL-12/IL-23 inhibitor, and strongly inhibits IL-12 in IFNg/SAC-stimulated human PBMCs and SAC-treated monkey PBMCs. Apilimod is a potent and highly selective PIKfyve inhibitor.
ARV-825 is a PROTAC connected by ligands for Cereblon and BRD4. ARV-825 binds to BD1 and BD2 of BRD4.
Birabresib (OTX-015) is a potent bromodomain (BRD2/3/4) inhibitor.
